        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-03-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-03-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="523" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d523">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.BB Palestine/3–1149: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Jerusalem</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Burdett</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Jerusalem</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-03-11">March 11,
                    1949</date>.</dateline>
                <p>216. According to Palestine <hi rend="italic">Post</hi> Ben Gurion stated in
                    Assembly speech yesterday “Jerusalem was part of Jewish state, and there was no
                    difference between Jerusalem and other parts of Israel. World recognition would
                    be sought for this”.</p>
                <p>Repeated Beirut 28, Baghdad 12, Damascus 11, Amman 16, pouched Cairo, Jidda.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Burdett</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
